## RO1: Discounts and Units Sold

**Research Objective:** Analyze whether higher discount percentages are associated with higher units sold.

| Element | Plan |
|---|---|
| Independent Variable | Discount percentage |
| Dependent Variable | Units sold |
| Controls | Product category, store location, day of week, holiday effect |
| Main Question | Do higher discounts lead to more units sold? |

---

## RO1: Wrangling and Visualization Plan

**Plan for data wrangling:**

- Convert discount percentage to numeric
- Create discount groups
- Summarize average units sold by discount group

**Plan for data visualization:**

- Scatterplot of discount percentage vs units sold
- Bar chart of average units sold by discount group
- Boxplot of units sold by discount group

```{r}
#| label: ro1-visual-template
#| eval: false

retail_tidy |> 
  ggplot(aes(x = discount_percentage, y = units_sold)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.3) +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = FALSE) +
  labs(
    title = "Discount Percentage vs Units Sold",
    x = "Discount Percentage",
    y = "Units Sold"
  )
```

