## RO2: Discounts and Sales Revenue

**Research Objective:** Examine whether discounts increase sales revenue.

| Element | Plan |
|---|---|
| Independent Variable | Discount percentage |
| Dependent Variable | Sales revenue |
| Controls | Units sold, product category, marketing spend |
| Main Question | Do discounts increase total revenue or only increase volume? |

---

## RO2: Wrangling and Visualization Plan

**Plan for data wrangling:**

- Group records by discount level
- Calculate average and total sales revenue
- Compare revenue across discount groups

**Plan for data visualization:**

- Bar chart of average revenue by discount group
- Scatterplot of discount percentage vs sales revenue
- Revenue comparison table

```{r}
#| label: ro2-visual-template
#| eval: false

retail_tidy |> 
  group_by(discount_group) |> 
  summarise(avg_revenue = mean(sales_revenue_usd, na.rm = TRUE)) |> 
  ggplot(aes(x = discount_group, y = avg_revenue)) +
  geom_col() +
  labs(
    title = "Average Sales Revenue by Discount Group",
    x = "Discount Group",
    y = "Average Sales Revenue"
  )
```

