## RO3: Discounts by Product Category

**Research Objective:** Compare the effect of discounts across product categories.

| Element | Plan |
|---|---|
| Independent Variables | Discount percentage, product category |
| Dependent Variable | Units sold or sales revenue |
| Grouping Variable | Product category |
| Main Question | Which product categories respond most strongly to discounts? |

---

## RO3: Wrangling and Visualization Plan

**Plan for data wrangling:**

- Group data by product category and discount group
- Calculate average units sold and average revenue
- Rank categories by discount response

**Plan for data visualization:**

- Faceted bar chart by product category
- Category-level comparison table
- Product category ranking chart

```{r}
#| label: ro3-visual-template
#| eval: false

retail_tidy |> 
  group_by(product_category, discount_group) |> 
  summarise(avg_units = mean(units_sold, na.rm = TRUE), .groups = "drop") |> 
  ggplot(aes(x = discount_group, y = avg_units)) +
  geom_col() +
  facet_wrap(~ product_category) +
  labs(
    title = "Average Units Sold by Discount Group and Product Category",
    x = "Discount Group",
    y = "Average Units Sold"
  )
```

