## RO4: Marketing Spend and Discount Performance

**Research Objective:** Analyze whether marketing spend strengthens the impact of discounts.

| Element | Plan |
|---|---|
| Independent Variables | Discount percentage, marketing spend |
| Dependent Variable | Sales revenue or units sold |
| Possible Interaction | Discount percentage × marketing spend |
| Main Question | Do discounts perform better when supported by higher marketing spend? |

---

## RO4: Wrangling and Visualization Plan

**Plan for data wrangling:**

- Create low, medium, and high marketing spend groups
- Compare sales outcomes across discount and marketing spend groups
- Test whether discount effectiveness changes with marketing support

**Plan for data visualization:**

- Scatterplot of marketing spend vs sales revenue
- Bar chart by marketing spend group and discount group
- Interaction-style line chart

```{r}
#| label: ro4-visual-template
#| eval: false

retail_tidy |> 
  mutate(
    marketing_group = ntile(marketing_spend_usd, 3),
    marketing_group = case_when(
      marketing_group == 1 ~ "Low marketing spend",
      marketing_group == 2 ~ "Medium marketing spend",
      marketing_group == 3 ~ "High marketing spend"
    )
  ) |> 
  group_by(marketing_group, discount_group) |> 
  summarise(avg_revenue = mean(sales_revenue_usd, na.rm = TRUE), .groups = "drop") |> 
  ggplot(aes(x = discount_group, y = avg_revenue, group = marketing_group)) +
  geom_line() +
  geom_point() +
  facet_wrap(~ marketing_group) +
  labs(
    title = "Discount Performance by Marketing Spend Group",
    x = "Discount Group",
    y = "Average Sales Revenue"
  )
```

